1. For the car to lock when leaving, the four doors and two sunroofs must be closed and the car should be stationary; 
2. The sensor range for locking/unlocking the car: the key must be no less than 2.5m from the front door handle when approaching, and 3.5m away when leaving; 
3. If the tailgate is opened separately while the other four doors are closed, auto unlock can only be enabled by meeting the above conditions. We recommend exiting from the front door after closing the tailgate; 
4. If you want to lock without powering down (via the mobile app), hold the key at a distance no further than 3.5m from the front door handle after getting out of the car, so as to avoid triggering power-off due to auto lock by standing at a distance greater than 3.5m; 
5. After key parking, the key should be carried at a close distance to the vehicle. After sensing the key signal, the vehicle will lock upon leaving
